WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.068 --> 00:00:03.435
Another body at
Yates' burial ground.

2
00:00:03.537 --> 00:00:05.301
Someone committed
this horrific crime

3
00:00:05.439 --> 00:00:07.840
<i>to piggyback it onto
crimes I've been accused of.</i>

4
00:00:08.041 --> 00:00:09.319
ROLLINS: <i>You
know who the killer is.</i>

5
00:00:09.343 --> 00:00:10.470
Dr. Carl Rudnick.

6
00:00:10.777 --> 00:00:12.737
Accusing the Deputy Chief
M.E. of rape and murder?

7
00:00:12.913 --> 00:00:14.753
You can't think I had
anything to do with this.

8
00:00:14.882 --> 00:00:16.908
Carl Rudnick.
you're under arrest.

9
00:00:17.718 --> 00:00:21.120
Something happened to Susie. She
was supposed to call this morning.

10
00:00:21.321 --> 00:00:23.132
YATES: (OVER PHONE)
<i>Rudnick's still in custody. isn't he?</i>

11
00:00:23.156 --> 00:00:24.522
No. he made bail last night.

12
00:00:24.958 --> 00:00:26.756
We're not sure it's Susie.

13
00:00:29.530 --> 00:00:30.554
We are now.

14
00:00:37.604 --> 00:00:39.436
NARRATOR: <i>In the
criminal justice system.</i>

15
00:00:39.540 --> 00:00:42.704
<i>sexually based offenses are
considered especially heinous.</i>

16
00:00:43.210 --> 00:00:44.439
<i>In New York City.</i>

17
00:00:44.545 --> 00:00:47.447
<i>the dedicated detectives who
investigate these vicious felonies</i>

18
00:00:47.548 --> 00:00:50.848
<i>are members of an elite squad
known as the Special Victims Unit.</i>

19
00:00:50.951 --> 00:00:52.419
<i>These are their stories.</i>

20
00:00:54.588 --> 00:00:56.548
COUNSELOR CALHOUN:
What the hell is going on here?

21
00:00:56.723 --> 00:00:58.214
BENSON: Exigent circumstances.

22
00:00:58.325 --> 00:01:01.784
COUNSELOR CALHOUN: Nice try. I
don't hear anyone screaming for help.

23
00:01:02.129 --> 00:01:04.189
You have a warrant to
search Dr. Rudnick's house?

24
00:01:04.298 --> 00:01:05.391
We had one yesterday.

25
00:01:05.499 --> 00:01:06.933
And now you need a new one.

26
00:01:07.034 --> 00:01:08.332
Really. Rita?

27
00:01:08.702 --> 00:01:11.035
We don't know that
Dr. Rudnick was involved.

28
00:01:11.538 --> 00:01:12.767
Where's your client. Rita?

29
00:01:13.106 --> 00:01:14.335
I haven't heard from him.

30
00:01:14.441 --> 00:01:17.570
He is the suspect
in this murder. okay?

31
00:01:18.145 --> 00:01:20.011
You hear from him.
you better let us know.

32
00:01:21.415 --> 00:01:23.145
The only legal obligation I have

33
00:01:23.250 --> 00:01:25.048
is to make sure that
he shows up at trial.

34
00:01:25.152 --> 00:01:29.283
You're claiming attorney-client
privilege for a psychopath.

35
00:01:29.389 --> 00:01:31.585
who's on the run.
who gutted a woman.

36
00:01:31.692 --> 00:01:32.853
I have no knowledge of that.

37
00:01:32.960 --> 00:01:36.124
and I have no knowledge of
any future acts he may commit.

38
00:01:36.229 --> 00:01:37.697
His car is missing.

39
00:01:37.798 --> 00:01:39.078
He's not answering
his telephone.

40
00:01:39.166 --> 00:01:41.533
We need to search
this house now.

41
00:01:41.635 --> 00:01:44.764
And you can. as soon
as you get a warrant.

42
00:01:58.552 --> 00:02:00.129
SONNY: Fin's at Real
Time checking traffic cams.

43
00:02:00.153 --> 00:02:01.587
Sarge is at Rudnick's townhouse.

44
00:02:01.688 --> 00:02:03.266
There's no sign of this
guy. He's in the wind.

45
00:02:03.290 --> 00:02:06.055
Yeah. well. he murdered
and dismembered Susie Frain.

46
00:02:06.159 --> 00:02:07.537
I wouldn't have
stuck around either.

47
00:02:07.561 --> 00:02:08.801
We're still missing a left leg.

48
00:02:17.204 --> 00:02:18.638
That's a calf.

49
00:02:18.939 --> 00:02:21.340
CHUNG: Sawed off at the
left knee. Not a lot of blood.

50
00:02:21.675 --> 00:02:22.768
Hmm.

51
00:02:22.976 --> 00:02:24.035
(CLEARS THROAT)

52
00:02:24.811 --> 00:02:26.211
You guys got this. right?

53
00:02:26.580 --> 00:02:27.604
Yeah. give me one second.

54
00:02:28.515 --> 00:02:29.608
(VOMITING)

55
00:02:29.716 --> 00:02:30.979
Oh. easy.

56
00:02:32.252 --> 00:02:33.584
You all right? Yeah.

57
00:02:34.655 --> 00:02:36.180
Yeah. I'm fine.

58
00:02:39.726 --> 00:02:42.161
I'm gonna drive us back. Okay?

59
00:02:45.465 --> 00:02:47.229
Twelve hours after
Rudnick posts bail.

60
00:02:47.334 --> 00:02:48.632
a potential prosecution witness

61
00:02:48.735 --> 00:02:50.279
is found in pieces
with the morning tide?

62
00:02:50.303 --> 00:02:51.447
We're well aware of the problem.

63
00:02:51.471 --> 00:02:53.372
ROLLINS: Counselor.
Where the hell is he?

64
00:02:53.473 --> 00:02:54.998
This is all we know. okay?

65
00:02:55.108 --> 00:02:57.186
He was last seen posting
bond at 8:00 p.m. last night.

66
00:02:57.210 --> 00:02:59.689
Yeah. Uber driver confirms dropping
him off at his Harlem townhouse.

67
00:02:59.713 --> 00:03:02.046
So sometime between
last night and this morning.

68
00:03:02.149 --> 00:03:03.845
he goes to Susie
Frain's apartment.

69
00:03:03.984 --> 00:03:05.543
He dismembers her.
he bags her body.

70
00:03:05.652 --> 00:03:07.964
dumps her in the water at Fort
Tilden. and then he disappears.

71
00:03:07.988 --> 00:03:09.432
ROLLINS: We've got
a BOLO out on his car.

72
00:03:09.456 --> 00:03:11.550
his credit. his bank
cards. So far. no hits.

73
00:03:11.658 --> 00:03:12.887
No sightings? No traffic cams?

74
00:03:12.993 --> 00:03:14.203
Does everyone know
he dresses in drag?

75
00:03:14.227 --> 00:03:16.219
We've alerted State
Troopers and the FBI.

76
00:03:16.329 --> 00:03:17.627
Oh. they already know.

77
00:03:18.131 --> 00:03:20.828
The M.E.'s office. the Mayor's
office. the people in my office.

78
00:03:20.934 --> 00:03:23.646
People are falling over themselves to
point fingers. (CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

79
00:03:23.670 --> 00:03:25.190
Okay. I get it. It's
a mess. all right?

80
00:03:25.238 --> 00:03:27.173
No leave. no
vacation. no... Just...

81
00:03:27.974 --> 00:03:30.239
Yes. I'll hold for the Governor.

82
00:03:31.044 --> 00:03:32.444
Find him. Okay.

83
00:03:34.448 --> 00:03:36.212
Wow. Somebody needs a vacation.

84
00:03:36.316 --> 00:03:37.750
You can't blame him.

85
00:03:37.851 --> 00:03:40.263
(CHUCKLES) I mean. the guy
jumps bail and then he kills our witness.

86
00:03:40.287 --> 00:03:43.416
Speaking of... We need to notify
Yates that his fiancée’s dead.

87
00:03:43.523 --> 00:03:46.123
Look. that's not a priority right
now. He'll find out on the news.

88
00:03:46.159 --> 00:03:48.424
I know he will. but
the photo. Sergeant.

89
00:03:48.528 --> 00:03:51.396
The photo that Rudnick sent to
Susie pretending he was Lena.

90
00:03:51.798 --> 00:03:53.232
CSU tore her house apart.

91
00:03:53.333 --> 00:03:54.410
They couldn't find it anywhere.

92
00:03:54.434 --> 00:03:55.545
Yeah. of course they couldn't.

93
00:03:55.569 --> 00:03:57.280
That's why Rudnick went to
her house in the first place.

94
00:03:57.304 --> 00:03:58.347
So check her phone records.

95
00:03:58.371 --> 00:03:59.582
Find out if she called Rudnick.

96
00:03:59.606 --> 00:04:01.984
SONNY: What. you think she
was using that photo for blackmail?

97
00:04:02.008 --> 00:04:04.375
You know she did not come
up with that idea on her own.

98
00:04:05.178 --> 00:04:06.771
Which is why I
need to talk to Yates.

99
00:04:06.880 --> 00:04:08.591
You know he's more open
when it's just the two of us.

100
00:04:08.615 --> 00:04:10.140
Nice try. Rollins.

101
00:04:17.290 --> 00:04:18.290
YATES: (SIGHS) <i>Susie.</i>

102
00:04:20.393 --> 00:04:21.952
Can I see the body?

103
00:04:22.529 --> 00:04:24.521
That's not gonna be
possible. Dr. Yates.

104
00:04:25.031 --> 00:04:26.966
Are you sure it was her?

105
00:04:27.134 --> 00:04:28.568
ROLLINS: We're sure. I'm sorry.

106
00:04:30.470 --> 00:04:32.803
So. we were hoping.
uh. to talk to you about

107
00:04:32.906 --> 00:04:35.432
your last conversation
with Susie Frain.

108
00:04:35.809 --> 00:04:37.437
Yes. of course.

109
00:04:37.878 --> 00:04:39.574
How did Rudnick kill her?

110
00:04:40.013 --> 00:04:41.173
Still waiting on the autopsy.

111
00:04:42.616 --> 00:04:46.553
You are? Could you ask the
M.E. to test her HCG levels?

112
00:04:47.454 --> 00:04:50.947
Excuse me? I'd like to know
whether Susie was pregnant.

113
00:04:51.057 --> 00:04:56.257
That afternoon in April. before
I was arrested. we made love.

114
00:04:56.363 --> 00:04:59.060
I could sense that
she was ovulating.

115
00:04:59.166 --> 00:05:03.467
When we had our conjugal. she
agreed to take a pregnancy test.

116
00:05:06.406 --> 00:05:09.376
It's quite possible that I
was going to be a father.

117
00:05:11.044 --> 00:05:12.512
and he took that from me.

118
00:05:22.622 --> 00:05:24.614
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

119
00:06:08.802 --> 00:06:09.826
You got something?

120
00:06:10.003 --> 00:06:11.027
Yeah. I got ahold of Fin.

121
00:06:11.137 --> 00:06:13.337
He and TARU have been going
through Rudnick's computers.

122
00:06:13.406 --> 00:06:16.001
finances. flagging every
credit card they could find.

123
00:06:16.109 --> 00:06:17.109
Okay. Any hits?

124
00:06:17.177 --> 00:06:18.387
Not yet. but they did find this.

125
00:06:18.411 --> 00:06:20.971
So. Dr. Crazy's been
wiring money from a trust

126
00:06:21.081 --> 00:06:23.526
to four different personal
accounts under four different names.

127
00:06:23.550 --> 00:06:25.310
So contact these people.
We're trying. Sarge.

128
00:06:25.352 --> 00:06:28.379
But. as of now. their only
known addresses are PO boxes.

129
00:06:28.488 --> 00:06:30.753
I mean. we can't find any
employers. phone listings.

130
00:06:30.857 --> 00:06:32.155
Okay. so they're false fronts.

131
00:06:32.259 --> 00:06:34.160
I just got something
from the DMV.

132
00:06:34.261 --> 00:06:35.729
See that Terry Fish
account up there?

133
00:06:35.829 --> 00:06:37.422
I just found a
Teresa Fish that has

134
00:06:37.564 --> 00:06:39.244
an apartment in the
same zip as the PO box.

135
00:06:39.299 --> 00:06:40.299
Great.

136
00:06:41.301 --> 00:06:43.133
Oh. Rudnick's a blonde now?

137
00:06:43.870 --> 00:06:47.034
ROLLINS: Teresa got her
license in October of last year.

138
00:06:47.140 --> 00:06:48.784
I'll put a BOLO out. You
know what. I'll do that.

139
00:06:48.808 --> 00:06:50.834
You two get up
to that apartment.

140
00:06:51.011 --> 00:06:53.037
If we get lucky. Rudnick
may be hiding there.

141
00:06:57.751 --> 00:06:59.185
Hey. you all right?

142
00:06:59.953 --> 00:07:01.197
Why wouldn't I be? I don't know.

143
00:07:01.221 --> 00:07:02.712
Usually you're two
steps ahead of me.

144
00:07:02.822 --> 00:07:04.600
and I've never seen you
queasy at a crime scene before.

145
00:07:04.624 --> 00:07:05.717
Yeah.

146
00:07:05.825 --> 00:07:08.090
I had a bad bagel
yesterday. I'm totally fine.

147
00:07:12.933 --> 00:07:15.596
MRS. CASEY: I wondered if
something happened to poor Terry.

148
00:07:15.702 --> 00:07:19.139
I ain't seen her in a while
here. maybe since. uh. April?

149
00:07:19.606 --> 00:07:21.905
Is she okay? I miss
her around here.

150
00:07:22.008 --> 00:07:23.567
You know her? You
talk to her much?

151
00:07:23.677 --> 00:07:25.145
Oh. is that a joke?

152
00:07:25.312 --> 00:07:27.032
Does it look like either
of us are laughing?

153
00:07:27.414 --> 00:07:31.613
Sounds like a joke.
Terry's mute. Deaf. too.

154
00:07:32.919 --> 00:07:34.239
She used to write
me little notes.

155
00:07:34.287 --> 00:07:36.279
you know. if she
needed something.

156
00:07:36.389 --> 00:07:38.187
But never a complaint.

157
00:07:38.291 --> 00:07:40.522
She paid her rent
a year in advance.

158
00:07:43.029 --> 00:07:44.258
Terry!

159
00:07:44.731 --> 00:07:48.327
Oh. what am I doing? It's
not like she can hear me.

160
00:08:08.254 --> 00:08:10.348
You lay this new floor in here?

161
00:08:10.457 --> 00:08:12.016
I told you she
was a good tenant.

162
00:08:12.125 --> 00:08:13.787
She must have
put that in herself.

163
00:08:13.893 --> 00:08:15.054
Yeah.

164
00:08:34.914 --> 00:08:36.075
Carisi.

165
00:08:37.283 --> 00:08:38.512
Hey. I found more wigs

166
00:08:38.618 --> 00:08:40.246
and floral print
dresses. lots of them.

167
00:08:40.887 --> 00:08:43.413
It's red hair. just
like Rachel Groves.

168
00:08:43.590 --> 00:08:46.116
and these look like
cutting marks to you?

169
00:08:46.226 --> 00:08:48.161
Totally. I'll call CSU.

170
00:08:51.931 --> 00:08:53.991
I got your message
about Rudnick's aliases.

171
00:08:54.100 --> 00:08:55.864
so I re-checked his
Jane Doe autopsies.

172
00:08:55.969 --> 00:08:57.665
The last one was in October.

173
00:08:58.138 --> 00:09:01.302
50-year-old homeless woman
found dead on the E train.

174
00:09:01.408 --> 00:09:02.842
Listed as natural causes.

175
00:09:02.942 --> 00:09:04.001
Never ID'd.

176
00:09:05.111 --> 00:09:08.843
Rudnick's paperwork says no
match on fingerprints or DNA.

177
00:09:09.149 --> 00:09:10.742
but I got a print hit

178
00:09:10.850 --> 00:09:13.319
on a New York City
food stamp application.

179
00:09:13.753 --> 00:09:14.948
Teresa Fish.

180
00:09:15.822 --> 00:09:18.986
Rudnick wanted to make sure
that nobody would miss her.

181
00:09:19.092 --> 00:09:20.822
so he could steal her identity.

182
00:09:21.294 --> 00:09:23.695
Identity thief. rapist. killer.

183
00:09:24.230 --> 00:09:26.859
The damage he's done to
this office. it makes me furious.

184
00:09:26.966 --> 00:09:28.644
Not to mention they brought
him up from Dade County

185
00:09:28.668 --> 00:09:30.432
instead of giving
you that promotion.

186
00:09:31.071 --> 00:09:32.664
You know. you should re-apply.

187
00:09:34.007 --> 00:09:37.500
Before I do that. I need
to rerun DNA and prints

188
00:09:37.610 --> 00:09:40.774
on every body he's ever
sent to Potter's Field.

189
00:09:41.114 --> 00:09:42.173
(SIGHS)

190
00:09:42.816 --> 00:09:43.943
Thank you. Melinda.

191
00:09:46.619 --> 00:09:50.386
You were right. One can see
pronounced gouges on this bottom layer.

192
00:09:50.490 --> 00:09:52.584
Any guess on what
the implement was?

193
00:09:52.692 --> 00:09:54.684
I'd say it's a
large. flat blade.

194
00:09:54.794 --> 00:09:56.319
Maybe a cleaver.

195
00:09:56.863 --> 00:09:58.661
Oh. A-ha.

196
00:09:58.865 --> 00:10:01.596
BENNETT: It's a pattern.
Wipe marks. strokes.

197
00:10:02.302 --> 00:10:04.622
So he tried to wipe off the
blood. maybe what. with bleach?

198
00:10:04.671 --> 00:10:07.334
Yeah. but he didn't get
it all. Hence the glow.

199
00:10:13.379 --> 00:10:14.379
(GRUNTING)

200
00:10:14.581 --> 00:10:15.844
Okay. Okay.

201
00:10:21.554 --> 00:10:22.886
Dried blood.

202
00:10:23.623 --> 00:10:25.501
Quite apparent something
barbarous happened here.

203
00:10:25.525 --> 00:10:26.959
Yes. Yeah.

204
00:10:27.327 --> 00:10:28.454
Hey. you up for a flight?

205
00:10:28.628 --> 00:10:29.789
No. not really.

206
00:10:29.896 --> 00:10:32.195
Tough luck. Our plane
leaves in 40 minutes.

207
00:10:32.298 --> 00:10:33.926
Rudnick just got
picked up in Syracuse

208
00:10:34.033 --> 00:10:35.524
