mother was dying in Canada.

215
00:10:51.985 --> 00:10:53.647
He stole a frigging
box of Coffee Nips.

216
00:10:53.753 --> 00:10:54.753
All right. I get it.

217
00:10:54.921 --> 00:10:55.965
We did give him a desk ticket.

218
00:10:55.989 --> 00:10:57.013
Good for you.

219
00:10:57.123 --> 00:10:58.682
Listen. Rollins. the
system was down.

220
00:10:58.791 --> 00:11:00.225
He said his mother was dying.

221
00:11:01.094 --> 00:11:02.460
All right. we've had a long day.

222
00:11:02.562 --> 00:11:04.039
The good news is
no one with that name

223
00:11:04.063 --> 00:11:05.508
got on a plane.
train. or rented a car.

224
00:11:05.532 --> 00:11:07.810
Did you check his other aliases?
'Cause he has at least four.

225
00:11:07.834 --> 00:11:09.928
We did. Look. we got this
entire town locked down.

226
00:11:10.036 --> 00:11:11.129
He's not going anywhere.

227
00:11:11.237 --> 00:11:13.570
Planes. trains. automobiles.
Did you check buses?

228
00:11:13.673 --> 00:11:15.266
A Meta Bus left an
hour ago for Buffalo.

229
00:11:15.441 --> 00:11:17.034
He could walk to
Canada from there.

230
00:11:17.143 --> 00:11:18.338
Yeah. What time's it arrive?

231
00:11:18.444 --> 00:11:20.723
It just left Rochester. It's gonna
be there in two-and-a-half hours.

232
00:11:20.747 --> 00:11:21.840
Gonna need a squad car now.

233
00:11:26.886 --> 00:11:28.252
Here comes our bus.

234
00:11:33.393 --> 00:11:36.329
You're the detectives from
New York? ROLLINS: Yeah.

235
00:11:36.729 --> 00:11:38.322
Bob Hencamp. Buffalo PD.

236
00:11:38.431 --> 00:11:39.975
Dominick Carisi. This
is Detective Rollins.

237
00:11:39.999 --> 00:11:41.399
Hi. there. We call her Sunny.

238
00:11:41.501 --> 00:11:43.402
Sunny Rollins? Okay.

239
00:11:43.970 --> 00:11:46.462
Troopers picked up the
bus on I-90 an hour ago.

240
00:11:46.573 --> 00:11:47.939
Followed at a discreet distance.

241
00:11:48.041 --> 00:11:49.100
So he's still on board?

242
00:11:49.209 --> 00:11:51.576
There was an E. Howard
credit card purchase in Syracuse.

243
00:11:51.678 --> 00:11:54.273
Bus didn't make any stops
between Rochester and here.

244
00:11:54.380 --> 00:11:56.458
Okay. Well. let's do this
thing. Nice and easy. all right?

245
00:11:56.482 --> 00:11:57.506
We don't wanna spook him.

246
00:12:02.155 --> 00:12:03.316
Dr. Rudnick.

247
00:12:03.423 --> 00:12:04.423
This is your guy?

248
00:12:04.591 --> 00:12:07.271
I'm Ellie Howard. and I fully
intend to pay my fine for shoplifting.

249
00:12:07.327 --> 00:12:08.556
Ms. Howard. stop.

250
00:12:08.661 --> 00:12:11.631
Why don't you come with
us. all right? We'll sort this out.

251
00:12:13.366 --> 00:12:15.028
Hands behind your back. please.

252
00:12:15.134 --> 00:12:16.227
Is that really necessary?

253
00:12:16.402 --> 00:12:17.529
Let him do his job.

254
00:12:24.444 --> 00:12:26.072
All right. come on.

255
00:12:31.084 --> 00:12:33.485
So. you got a
cross-dressing rapist/murderer

256
00:12:33.586 --> 00:12:34.849
in your M.E.'s office?

257
00:12:34.954 --> 00:12:37.583
You guys down in New York
City really are progressive.

258
00:12:37.690 --> 00:12:39.181
Yeah. He say anything?

259
00:12:39.359 --> 00:12:40.884
He bitched when we searched him.

260
00:12:40.994 --> 00:12:44.294
Maybe because he had a
money belt with $64.000 in cash.

261
00:12:44.397 --> 00:12:46.298
So why's he shoplifting
Coffee Nips then?

262
00:12:46.399 --> 00:12:48.959
(EXHALES) That's
the $64.000 question.

263
00:12:50.069 --> 00:12:53.039
Just give me a minute to finish
paperwork. and he's all yours.

264
00:12:54.807 --> 00:12:56.332
You have a cause of death?

265
00:12:56.676 --> 00:13:00.374
Manner. homicide. No one
ends up like this accidentally.

266
00:13:00.480 --> 00:13:02.472
Cause of death. exsanguination.

267
00:13:03.316 --> 00:13:04.784
So she bled out
when he cut her up?

268
00:13:04.884 --> 00:13:07.376
No. The dismemberment
occurred postmortem.

269
00:13:08.388 --> 00:13:10.516
Problem is I can't
find the initial wound.

270
00:13:10.957 --> 00:13:13.654
Most likely trauma to
the femoral vein or artery.

271
00:13:13.760 --> 00:13:15.388
Stab wound. Maybe gunshot.

272
00:13:15.495 --> 00:13:16.895
To the missing left thigh?

273
00:13:16.996 --> 00:13:19.727
I would guess that's why
Rudnick made it disappear.

274
00:13:20.533 --> 00:13:21.831
There's something else.

275
00:13:22.335 --> 00:13:24.270
Susie's tox screen
came back clean.

276
00:13:24.937 --> 00:13:27.133
but her HCG levels were high.

277
00:13:27.573 --> 00:13:28.802
She was pregnant.

278
00:13:32.045 --> 00:13:33.069
(SIGHS)

279
00:13:34.814 --> 00:13:36.094
We aren't actually
going to drive

280
00:13:36.215 --> 00:13:37.559
all the way back to
Manhattan. are we?

281
00:13:37.583 --> 00:13:38.676
ROLLINS: Shut up.

282
00:13:38.885 --> 00:13:40.683
You took the bus up
here anyway. right?

283
00:13:40.787 --> 00:13:43.120
Yes. when I was
traveling incognito.

284
00:13:43.222 --> 00:13:44.747
Hey. what were you
thinking. anyway?

285
00:13:44.924 --> 00:13:46.449
Skipping out on
a $2 million bail.

286
00:13:46.559 --> 00:13:47.670
Well. what were they thinking?

287
00:13:47.694 --> 00:13:48.737
They charge me with two murders.

288
00:13:48.761 --> 00:13:50.881
then let me go? Who wouldn't
run? (CELL PHONE RINGING)

289
00:13:53.433 --> 00:13:54.560
Hey. Sarge.

290
00:13:55.168 --> 00:13:56.796
Yeah. we're making
pretty good time.

291
00:13:56.903 --> 00:13:59.423
As long as we don't get pulled
over. we should be back around...

292
00:13:59.472 --> 00:14:01.964
Wait. hold on. let
me check my app.

293
00:14:02.275 --> 00:14:03.709
Noon. Wait. hold on.

294
00:14:03.976 --> 00:14:06.571
Noon! Noon. All right.
we'll be back around noon.

295
00:14:07.647 --> 00:14:09.582
All right. Copy that.

296
00:14:11.951 --> 00:14:13.817
They found his car.

297
00:14:13.920 --> 00:14:15.218
Why are you whispering?

298
00:14:15.321 --> 00:14:16.481
Rudnick. they found your car.

299
00:14:16.756 --> 00:14:19.157
Well. give
yourselves a gold star.

300
00:14:20.827 --> 00:14:22.386
We sure it's Rudnick's?

301
00:14:22.495 --> 00:14:24.191
Plates and all
identifiers were stripped.

302
00:14:24.297 --> 00:14:25.674
but we got the VIN
off the engine block.

303
00:14:25.698 --> 00:14:26.927
Okay. so why here?

304
00:14:27.033 --> 00:14:29.161
The train to the
plane's a block away.

305
00:14:29.268 --> 00:14:30.827
Oh. so. had we
found this any earlier.

306
00:14:31.003 --> 00:14:32.596
we would have
been searching JFK.

307
00:14:32.705 --> 00:14:34.970
While he got across the
border on his Meta Bus.

308
00:14:35.074 --> 00:14:37.543
He's not stupid.
but he was in a rush.

309
00:14:37.643 --> 00:14:42.547
He left blood. Now it's just
a trace. but that's all I need.

310
00:14:42.648 --> 00:14:44.674
BENSON: Great. I'll call Barba.

311
00:14:46.285 --> 00:14:49.050
A young man like
yourself working at SVU.

312
00:14:49.655 --> 00:14:51.123
That has to be depressing.

313
00:14:51.224 --> 00:14:52.248
You work in a morgue.

314
00:14:52.358 --> 00:14:53.451
I find peace in that.

315
00:14:54.594 --> 00:14:55.823
I bring closure to people.

316
00:14:55.928 --> 00:14:57.556
Yeah. when you're
not killing them.

317
00:14:57.663 --> 00:14:59.894
Death. in its way. is
the ultimate closure.

318
00:15:00.700 --> 00:15:02.328
Is that a confession?

319
00:15:03.569 --> 00:15:04.730
Thanks.

320
00:15:08.207 --> 00:15:09.952
SONNY: You sure you don't
want something more substantial?

321
00:15:09.976 --> 00:15:11.376
Hmm. Yes. I'm sure.

322
00:15:13.279 --> 00:15:15.457
Don't you people think about
what you eat? ROLLINS: Nope.

323
00:15:15.481 --> 00:15:18.076
RUDNICK: Well. you
should. All that cholesterol.

324
00:15:18.184 --> 00:15:19.424
I could tell you both right now

325
00:15:19.452 --> 00:15:20.629
what your livers
are going to look like

326
00:15:20.653 --> 00:15:22.053
when they're
eventually on the slab.

327
00:15:22.121 --> 00:15:24.056
You know what? Don't.

328
00:15:26.959 --> 00:15:28.188
I don't mean to be a nuisance.

329
00:15:28.294 --> 00:15:29.887
but may I use the facilities?

330
00:15:32.165 --> 00:15:33.165
(SCOFFS)

331
00:15:35.835 --> 00:15:36.835
(EXHALES)

332
00:15:36.936 --> 00:15:38.734
Oh. hey. Still occupied.

333
00:15:39.439 --> 00:15:41.169
All right. look. it's my uncle.

334
00:15:41.274 --> 00:15:43.072
I'll see if I can hurry
him along. Okay?

335
00:15:44.811 --> 00:15:47.042
RUDNICK: This is
unfortunate. (SIGHS)

336
00:15:48.147 --> 00:15:50.309
They think I killed that
woman and cut her up.

337
00:15:51.717 --> 00:15:53.379
I don't understand why.

338
00:15:54.821 --> 00:15:58.121
Well. of course. I do
understand. It's still offensive.

339
00:15:58.224 --> 00:15:59.988
And so are they.

340
00:16:01.160 --> 00:16:02.160
(SIGHS)

341
00:16:02.261 --> 00:16:04.321
Quiet. Doctor. Quiet.

342
00:16:06.132 --> 00:16:07.395
Good man.

343
00:16:12.472 --> 00:16:15.840
Hey. Doc. Come
on. we gotta go. Oh.

344
00:16:16.476 --> 00:16:18.411
Could I trouble
you for my phone?

345
00:16:19.612 --> 00:16:21.376
I need to call my lawyer.

346
00:16:22.315 --> 00:16:24.113
Mr. Barba? RAFAEL: Uh-huh.

347
00:16:25.318 --> 00:16:26.513
(CHUCKLES)

348
00:16:27.053 --> 00:16:28.282
Rita.

349
00:16:29.856 --> 00:16:31.620
You have one hell of a client.

350
00:16:31.958 --> 00:16:34.236
Kills a pregnant witness and
tries to cross the border in a dress.

351
00:16:34.260 --> 00:16:36.161
Dr. Rudnick was out on bond.

352
00:16:36.262 --> 00:16:38.424
He was simply taking
in the sights of Buffalo.

353
00:16:38.598 --> 00:16:39.691
Uh-huh.

354
00:16:40.600 --> 00:16:42.068
We have a DNA match

355
00:16:42.168 --> 00:16:44.433
from Rachel Groves'
hair and blood

356
00:16:44.604 --> 00:16:46.869
on the kitchen floor of an
apartment that he leased.

357
00:16:46.973 --> 00:16:50.239
He's an M.E. He
autopsied her body.

358
00:16:50.343 --> 00:16:51.902
It could be cross-contamination.

359
00:16:52.011 --> 00:16:54.037
Well. he didn't
autopsy Susie Frain.

360
00:16:54.146 --> 00:16:55.580
and we found her
blood in his car.

361
00:16:55.681 --> 00:16:57.343
They were old friends.

362
00:16:57.450 --> 00:17:00.477
He gave her a ride. she
bled from a paper cut.

363
00:17:00.753 --> 00:17:02.415
Both those cases
were circumstantial.

364
00:17:02.522 --> 00:17:06.050
and don't get me started on
a 13-year-old body in a wall.

365
00:17:06.158 --> 00:17:07.751
So why are you here. Rita?

366
00:17:08.327 --> 00:17:11.024
You have an M.E. accused
of being a serial killer.

367
00:17:11.130 --> 00:17:14.589
The last thing your bosses
want is a long. drawn out trial.

368
00:17:15.234 --> 00:17:18.500
And these headlines?
How are your migraines?

369
00:17:25.411 --> 00:17:26.936
Your solution is?

370
00:17:27.046 --> 00:17:30.539
Dr. Rudnick pleads to one
count of tampering with evidence

371
00:17:30.650 --> 00:17:34.143
and one count of
unlawful disposal of a body.

372
00:17:34.253 --> 00:17:36.984
This goes away as
quietly as possible.

373
00:17:37.089 --> 00:17:38.216
Misdemeanors?

374
00:17:39.225 --> 00:17:40.716
He killed three women.

375
00:17:43.162 --> 00:17:45.774
I can offer manslaughter. Twenty
years on each. served concurrently.

376
00:17:45.798 --> 00:17:47.426
A public defender
can get as much.

377
00:17:47.533 --> 00:17:49.058
He is paying for more than that.

378
00:17:52.305 --> 00:17:54.665
I hope there's enough money
in the world. Rita. I really do.

379
00:17:57.476 --> 00:17:59.342
You better hope you
don't get a conviction.

380
00:17:59.445 --> 00:18:02.210
because if you do. every
case Dr. Rudnick touched

381
00:18:02.315 --> 00:18:05.183
will be subject to an appeal.
starting with Greg Yates.

382
00:18:10.690 --> 00:18:12.454
I was so worried

383
00:18:13.492 --> 00:18:15.825
about what might
happen to Susie.

384
00:18:17.029 --> 00:18:18.520
She was always so trusting.

385
00:18:18.631 --> 00:18:20.998
She never saw the
dark side of people.

386
00:18:21.867 --> 00:18:23.335
In Dr. Rudnick?

387
00:18:27.373 --> 00:18:30.002
What did she say to
you when you last spoke?

388
00:18:31.143 --> 00:18:35.604
She firmly believed
that if she asked him.

389
00:18:36.215 --> 00:18:39.185
he would work to set me
free in exchange for the photo.

390
00:18:39.285 --> 00:18:41.481
I knew she was walking
into the lion's den.

391
00:18:42.321 --> 00:18:43.789
but she wouldn't listen. I...

392
00:18:44.724 --> 00:18:47.489
I think she wanted me out to
be there when she gave birth.

393
00:18:47.994 --> 00:18:50.725
So she told you she was
pregnant? No. (CHUCKLES)

394
00:18:51.230 --> 00:18:53.631
She didn't need to. I knew.

395
00:18:55.034 --> 00:18:57.469
She had a slightly
different scent.

396
00:18:59.138 --> 00:19:00.401
like you do.

397
00:19:03.075 --> 00:19:05.203
How far along
are you. Detective?

398
00:19:31.070 --> 00:19:32.070
(SIGHS)

399
00:19:36.976 --> 00:19:38.000
(CHUCKLES)

400
00:19:44.216 --> 00:19:46.185
JUDGE: Ms. Calhoun.
you ready to proceed?

401
00:19:46.285 --> 00:19:48.015
We are. Your Honor.
JUDGE: Mr. Barba?

402
00:19:48.120 --> 00:19:50.720
Your Honor. in addition to the
two standing charges of murder one.

403
00:19:50.790 --> 00:19:54.249
the defendant is now charged
with the murder of Susie Frain.

404
00:19:54.560 --> 00:19:55.960
Dr. Rudnick. how do you plead?

405
00:19:56.295 --> 00:19:58.127
I apologize for being
late. Your Honor.

406
00:19:58.230 --> 00:19:59.994
John Buchanan for the defense.

407
00:20:00.566 --> 00:20:02.034
My client pleads not guilty.

408
00:20:02.201 --> 00:20:03.669
JUDGE: I know who
you are. Counselor.

409
00:20:03.936 --> 00:20:06.303
But I'm not a fan of
courtroom theatrics.

410
00:20:06.405 --> 00:20:07.930
What's going on
here. Ms. Calhoun?

411
00:20:08.040 --> 00:20:11.909
I just need a moment
to confer with my client.

412
00:20:12.011 --> 00:20:13.445
So he is still your client?

413
00:20:13.546 --> 00:20:16.072
He is. Your Honor.
Dr. Rudnick has retained us both.

414
00:20:16.182 --> 00:20:17.445
You have?

415
00:20:17.616 --> 00:20:18.960
Rita. the state saw
fit to double down.

416
00:20:18.984 --> 00:20:20.577
I thought it prudent
to do the same.

417
00:20:20.686 --> 00:20:22.416
You both have my
complete confidence.

418
00:20:22.521 --> 00:20:23.716
JUDGE: May we proceed?

419
00:20:24.423 --> 00:20:26.016
People on bail? RAFAEL: Remand.

420
00:20:26.325 --> 00:20:28.624
While out on bail. the
defendant murdered

421
00:20:28.728 --> 00:20:30.629
and dismembered a
prosecution witness.

422
00:20:30.730 --> 00:20:32.028
Another wild accusation.

423
00:20:32.131 --> 00:20:34.600
More to the point. he is
free to travel within the state.

424
00:20:34.700 --> 00:20:36.828
He has violated no court order.

425
00:20:36.936 --> 00:20:38.063
That is absolutely correct.

426
00:20:38.237 --> 00:20:39.330
JUDGE: Enough. Doctor.

427
00:20:39.438 --> 00:20:41.236
Your bail was a privilege.

428
00:20:41.340 --> 00:20:44.469
It has just been revoked.
You are remanded to Rikers.

429
00:20:44.577 --> 00:20:48.036
In that case. I have a motion
to separate these three charges.

430
00:20:48.147 --> 00:20:49.410
As do I.

431
00:20:49.515 --> 00:20:53.384
Coordinate and I'll let the
presiding judge know what he's in for.

432
00:20:53.486 --> 00:20:54.818
Good day. (GAVEL BANGS)

433
00:20:59.859 --> 00:21:03.125
Hey. missed you in court. Yeah.

434
00:21:04.230 --> 00:21:06.392
Hey. you look green.
Have a ginger ale.

435
00:21:08.067 --> 00:21:09.365
Yeah. I'm good.

436
00:21:12.638 --> 00:21:14.163
So. have you told anybody yet?

437
00:21:22.515 --> 00:21:23.710
Nope.

438
00:21:27.386 --> 00:21:28.547
I just found out.

439
00:21:32.057 --> 00:21:34.891
And not that it's
any of your business.

440
00:21:34.994 --> 00:21:36.434
but. you know.
it's not Nick's. so...

441
00:21:36.662 --> 00:21:37.925
Okay. Yeah.

442
00:21:38.764 --> 00:21:39.891
What are you gonna do?

443
00:21:40.332 --> 00:21:41.891
I'm not gonna do anything.

444
00:21:42.735 --> 00:21:45.000
Well. you might
wanna tell the sarge.

445
00:21:51.610 --> 00:21:54.637
Whiskey? Does that
mean it's bad news?

446
00:21:54.880 --> 00:21:57.475
(SIGHS) Rudnick's dream
team just got their first win.

447
00:21:57.583 --> 00:21:58.760
The judge granted their motion

448
00:21:58.784 --> 00:21:59.928
to separate out
the three charges.

449
00:21:59.952 --> 00:22:02.183
How? There's a clear pattern.

450
00:22:02.288 --> 00:22:03.483
(SIGHS) Not really.

451
00:22:04.623 --> 00:22:06.922
The murders are
spread out over 13 years.

452
00:22:07.193 --> 00:22:08.713
and the motives are
arguably different.

453
00:22:09.328 --> 00:22:11.854
Lena was his fiancée.
Susie was blackmailing him.

454
00:22:11.964 --> 00:22:13.899
and Rachel. she was
just easy pickings.

455
00:22:13.999 --> 00:22:15.377
Crime of opportunity.
Okay. I get it.

456
00:22:15.401 --> 00:22:17.801
So the Judge thought that
linking the three together would be

457
00:22:17.837 --> 00:22:20.197
more prejudicial than probative.
Prejudicial than probative.

458
00:22:20.973 --> 00:22:23.636
Okay. so what do
you need from me?

459
00:22:23.976 --> 00:22:26.878
A thigh. Establish
cause of death.

460
00:22:27.646 --> 00:22:28.978
Susie Frain is
our strongest case.

461
00:22:29.114 --> 00:22:31.913
The thigh is gone.
but you don't need it.

462
00:22:32.818 --> 00:22:34.116
He cut her up. Barba.

463
00:22:34.220 --> 00:22:36.815
I don't care how good
those lawyers think they are.

464
00:22:37.156 --> 00:22:41.287
when the jury sees what he
did to that woman. he's done.

465
00:22:44.930 --> 00:22:46.125
(SIGHS)

466
00:22:49.001 --> 00:22:50.761
RAFAEL: <i>Were you
able to identify the victim?</i>

467
00:22:51.036 --> 00:22:53.198
Yes. In another bag we opened.

468
00:22:53.305 --> 00:22:56.469
we found the decapitated
head of Susie Frain.

469
00:22:57.243 --> 00:22:58.438
It was

470
00:22:59.445 --> 00:23:02.506
one of the most gruesome crime
scenes that I've ever witnessed.

471
00:23:02.615 --> 00:23:03.615
Objection.

472
00:23:04.350 --> 00:23:06.717
These injuries occurred
after Ms. Frain's death.

473
00:23:07.419 --> 00:23:09.217
They have no bearing
on the murder charge

474
00:23:09.388 --> 00:23:11.186
and serve only to
prejudice this jury.

475
00:23:11.457 --> 00:23:14.188
Overruled. I'll
allow. up to a point.

476
00:23:14.560 --> 00:23:16.280
And I wanna remind
the jury that you're here

477
00:23:16.428 --> 00:23:18.124
to determine the
facts of the murder

478
00:23:18.230 --> 00:23:21.166
and not what happened
to the body postmortem.

479
00:23:21.734 --> 00:23:25.364
Sergeant Benson. the body
on the beach was Susie Frain?

480
00:23:25.471 --> 00:23:29.067
Yes. without a doubt.
DNA links all the pieces.

481
00:23:29.642 --> 00:23:31.008
Nothing further.

482
00:23:38.117 --> 00:23:39.415
Good morning. Sergeant.

483
00:23:40.152 --> 00:23:41.848
When you first met Ms. Frain.

484
00:23:41.954 --> 00:23:44.480
it was in connection with
another murder case. correct?

485
00:23:44.590 --> 00:23:45.614
It was.

486
00:23:45.724 --> 00:23:50.128
The brutal kidnapping. rape. and
murder of a Chicago PD employee

487
00:23:50.229 --> 00:23:52.596
by Ms. Frain's
fiancé. Greg Yates.

488
00:23:52.965 --> 00:23:54.126
Yes.

489
00:23:54.233 --> 00:23:56.600
Did Ms. Frain
maintain his innocence

490
00:23:56.769 --> 00:23:59.136
even after
Dr. Yates' conviction?

491
00:23:59.238 --> 00:24:00.297
Objection. Relevance.

492
00:24:00.406 --> 00:24:02.932
Your Honor. I intend
to show a direct line

493
00:24:03.042 --> 00:24:07.207
between Ms. Frain's pathological
desire to clear her fiancé

494
00:24:07.746 --> 00:24:09.772
and the events
that led to her death.

495
00:24:10.282 --> 00:24:11.614
I'll allow.

496
00:24:11.951 --> 00:24:13.681
Did Ms. Frain ever become aware

497
00:24:13.786 --> 00:24:18.622
that Dr. Carl Rudnick was the
Deputy Chief M.E. for Manhattan

498
00:24:18.724 --> 00:24:22.525
who had supervised the
autopsies of Dr. Yates' victims?

499
00:24:22.628 --> 00:24:24.358
Yes. and I know
that it's your job

500
00:24:24.463 --> 00:24:25.540
to try to make a
connection between the two.

501
00:24:25.564 --> 00:24:27.533
Well. so let me do my job.

502
00:24:29.068 --> 00:24:30.502
And after that.

503
00:24:30.936 --> 00:24:34.236
did you and ADA Barba

504
00:24:34.340 --> 00:24:36.502
helpfully arrange
for a conjugal visit

505
00:24:36.608 --> 00:24:39.578
between Ms. Frain and Dr. Yates?

506
00:24:39.678 --> 00:24:40.976
We did.

507
00:24:41.380 --> 00:24:43.849
Once reunited. did
they both spontaneously

508
00:24:44.016 --> 00:24:46.451
accuse Dr. Rudnick
of a series of crimes?

509
00:24:46.552 --> 00:24:48.997
Yes. but there were also two other
women who had been murdered.

510
00:24:49.021 --> 00:24:50.501
COUNSELOR
BUCHANAN: So. is it possible

511
00:24:51.557 --> 00:24:54.686
that they were colluding
to incriminate Dr. Rudnick

512
00:24:55.194 --> 00:24:57.857
in hopes of discrediting
him. and thus

513
00:24:58.697 --> 00:25:00.723
bolstering Yates'
chance for an appeal?

514
00:25:00.966 --> 00:25:02.400
Objection. Speculation.

515
00:25:03.135 --> 00:25:04.296
Is it?

516
00:25:05.104 --> 00:25:06.504
Withdrawn.

517
00:25:07.740 --> 00:25:10.266
Nothing further.
Thank you. Sergeant.

518
00:25:19.818 --> 00:25:21.343
Susie Frain was cooperating with

519
00:25:21.520 --> 00:25:23.098
a separate investigation
into Dr. Rudnick.

520
00:25:23.122 --> 00:25:24.590
Objection. Your Honor.

521
00:25:24.690 --> 00:25:26.181
This line goes
directly to motive.

522
00:25:26.291 --> 00:25:28.283
I'll allow. but only
in that context.

523
00:25:29.261 --> 00:25:31.059
In what way was Ms.
Frain cooperating?

524
00:25:31.163 --> 00:25:32.654
She was searching for photos

525
00:25:32.765 --> 00:25:35.360
which we believed would provide
evidence against Dr. Rudnick.

526
00:25:35.467 --> 00:25:37.979
but she was murdered before she
had the chance to deliver them to us.

527
00:25:38.003 --> 00:25:40.768
Did you find these
photos in her home?

528
00:25:42.041 --> 00:25:44.476
No. but as crime
scene pictures show...

529
00:25:44.576 --> 00:25:46.738
People's exhibit
47A. 47B. Your Honor.

530
00:25:46.845 --> 00:25:49.144
Objection. This is prejudicial.

531
00:25:49.248 --> 00:25:50.443
It's a crime scene.

532
00:25:50.549 --> 00:25:52.017
Agreed. Overruled.

533
00:25:53.118 --> 00:25:56.577
So. you can see her
ransacked memento boxes.

534
00:25:56.688 --> 00:25:58.486
And we also later
obtained security footage

535
00:25:58.657 --> 00:26:00.455
from her mini-storage facility.

536
00:26:00.559 --> 00:26:01.788
People's exhibit 48A.

537
00:26:01.894 --> 00:26:05.387
Where you can see the victim
had retrieved those same boxes

538
00:26:05.497 --> 00:26:06.897
the day before she was murdered.

539
00:26:06.999 --> 00:26:08.558
So we believe whoever killed her

540
00:26:08.734 --> 00:26:10.293
took the incriminating
photos with him.

541
00:26:10.402 --> 00:26:12.462
Objection. Pure speculation.

542
00:26:12.571 --> 00:26:14.836
Sustained. Jury will disregard.

543
00:26:18.410 --> 00:26:19.537
Nothing further.

544
00:26:19.645 --> 00:26:22.581
You just said that Ms. Frain had
agreed to search for these photos.

545
00:26:22.681 --> 00:26:25.014
Is there any reason to
think that she found them?

546
00:26:25.117 --> 00:26:28.110
Sergeant Benson and I were
informed of that fact by Dr. Yates.

547
00:26:28.220 --> 00:26:31.520
Dr. Yates? You mean
the convicted murderer?

548
00:26:32.891 --> 00:26:34.257
I see from the prison logs

549
00:26:34.359 --> 00:26:38.888
that you visited Dr. Yates a half a
dozen times in the last few weeks.

550
00:26:39.198 --> 00:26:42.066
I was hoping he could help me
with a number of unsolved cases.

551
00:26:42.167 --> 00:26:44.159
Two of those visits you
undertook on your own.

552
00:26:44.269 --> 00:26:47.762
Is that common practice
for a female NYPD detective?

553
00:26:49.842 --> 00:26:51.606
He was more open to me that way.

554
00:26:51.710 --> 00:26:53.235
So he confided in you?

555
00:26:53.946 --> 00:26:56.040
Did he also enlist
you to help him

556
00:26:56.148 --> 00:26:59.209
get a conjugal
visit with Ms. Frain?

557
00:26:59.651 --> 00:27:00.651
ROLLINS: Sure.

558
00:27:00.752 --> 00:27:02.220
Given that. it seems fair to say

559
00:27:02.321 --> 00:27:04.847
that you had a
relationship with Mr. Yates.

560
00:27:05.390 --> 00:27:06.722
Not in the way you mean.

561
00:27:06.825 --> 00:27:08.453
Oh? How do I mean it? Objection.

562
00:27:08.894 --> 00:27:10.294
I'll rephrase.

563
00:27:10.629 --> 00:27:12.564
Did anyone in your
squad ever think

564
00:27:12.664 --> 00:27:14.792
that Mr. Yates was
toying with you?

565
00:27:14.900 --> 00:27:17.529
Attempting to
implicate Dr. Rudnick

566
00:27:17.636 --> 00:27:20.333
in an effort to
exonerate himself?

567
00:27:21.840 --> 00:27:24.036
All informants have an agenda.

568
00:27:24.376 --> 00:27:25.935
Good detectives

569
00:27:27.546 --> 00:27:29.242
evaluate their credibility.

570
00:27:29.615 --> 00:27:32.312
Your answer is yes.
then? RAFAEL: Objection.

571
00:27:33.886 --> 00:27:36.617
Withdrawn. I'll quit
while I'm ahead.

572
00:27:42.828 --> 00:27:44.626
Hey. you okay?

573
00:27:45.831 --> 00:27:48.528
Yeah. I thought it was Rudnick
on trial. Not Yates or me.

574
00:27:48.800 --> 00:27:50.291
Lot of pressure up there.

575
00:27:51.236 --> 00:27:52.431
It is.

576
00:27:53.805 --> 00:27:55.569
Also. um. (EXHALES)

577
00:27:56.074 --> 00:27:57.133
I'm pregnant.

578
00:27:58.777 --> 00:28:00.006
Wow!

579
00:28:00.546 --> 00:28:02.481
Not Nick's. If you...

580
00:28:03.582 --> 00:28:04.811
Okay.

581
00:28:05.717 --> 00:28:07.208
Thanks for telling me.

582
00:28:07.553 --> 00:28:09.886
And I know. with the
squad being short-handed.

583
00:28:09.988 --> 00:28:12.958
it's not the best time for
you. but I wanna promise you.

584
00:28:13.058 --> 00:28:15.027
this is not gonna affect
my ability to do my job.

585
00:28:15.127 --> 00:28:17.289
Well. actually. it is.
Amanda. You know...

586
00:28:17.396 --> 00:28:19.456
Yeah. of course.
But I just meant...

587
00:28:19.565 --> 00:28:22.262
Look. I know you're
gonna fight me on this.

588
00:28:22.367 --> 00:28:23.545
but as soon as the
department hears.

589
00:28:23.569 --> 00:28:25.367
they're gonna put
you on restricted duty.

590
00:28:25.470 --> 00:28:26.961
Can't we wait to tell them?

591
00:28:29.007 --> 00:28:30.942
I just wanna work
until the last minute.

592
00:28:31.944 --> 00:28:33.970
I know what a hard
worker you are.

593
00:28:36.014 --> 00:28:38.279
That's a really
good thing 'cause...

594
00:28:38.584 --> 00:28:40.712
Because being a single mom is...

595
00:28:41.587 --> 00:28:42.816
It's not easy.

596
00:28:44.656 --> 00:28:45.988
Well. I may not be on my own.

597
00:28:46.091 --> 00:28:48.925
(STUTTERS) My mom might
actually move up to New York.

598
00:28:49.194 --> 00:28:51.595
Good. good. Yeah. (SIGHS)

599
00:28:52.264 --> 00:28:55.564
Well. I want you to know.
I'm really happy for you.

600
00:28:56.902 --> 00:29:02.102
And. you know. if you want
or need to talk about anything.

601
00:29:03.842 --> 00:29:05.003
I'm here.

602
00:29:06.878 --> 00:29:07.902
Okay.

603
00:29:15.053 --> 00:29:16.385
Susie Frain's cause of death

604
00:29:16.488 --> 00:29:18.787
was exsanguination.
She bled out.

605
00:29:18.890 --> 00:29:20.586
Yet you were unable
to determine where

606
00:29:20.692 --> 00:29:22.285
the initial wound was
made. Dr. Warner?

607
00:29:22.394 --> 00:29:24.863
Correct. I believe
it was in the piece

608
00:29:24.963 --> 00:29:27.364
of Susie Frain's thigh
that remains missing.

609
00:29:27.833 --> 00:29:29.563
What made you come
to that conclusion?

610
00:29:29.668 --> 00:29:31.534
The lack of blood in
her other body parts.

611
00:29:32.337 --> 00:29:36.206
And how many different body
parts were you able to examine?

612
00:29:36.308 --> 00:29:40.109
Objection. The prosecution
keeps trying to poison this jury

613
00:29:40.212 --> 00:29:41.723
with what happened
to the victim's body.

614
00:29:41.747 --> 00:29:44.512
Overruled. but let's
move it along. Mr. Barba.

615
00:29:45.417 --> 00:29:48.148
Despite being unable to
locate the initial wound.

616
00:29:48.253 --> 00:29:49.846
what did you list
as manner of death?

617
00:29:49.955 --> 00:29:51.253
Homicide.

618
00:29:51.356 --> 00:29:53.951
No one ends up cut
into pieces like this

619
00:29:54.126 --> 00:29:56.721
after an accidental
or natural death.

620
00:29:57.095 --> 00:29:58.586
Nothing further.

621
00:29:59.031 --> 00:30:00.329
COUNSELOR BUCHANAN: Dr. Warner.

622
00:30:01.600 --> 00:30:05.002
both Ms. Frain's
and my client's blood

623
00:30:05.103 --> 00:30:06.662
were found in Ms. Frain's home.

624
00:30:08.307 --> 00:30:10.037
Isn't that right? WARNER: Yes.

625
00:30:10.709 --> 00:30:12.371
Defense exhibit 13.

626
00:30:13.945 --> 00:30:16.437
My client had defensive
wounds on his hand

627
00:30:16.615 --> 00:30:19.141
and forearms when
you examined him.

628
00:30:19.851 --> 00:30:21.080
WARNER: Yes. he did.

629
00:30:21.253 --> 00:30:23.950
However. I can't tell you how
he sustained those injuries.

630
00:30:24.056 --> 00:30:25.422
Just like you can't tell us

631
00:30:25.524 --> 00:30:28.153
how Ms. Frain
sustained her fatal injury.

632
00:30:28.260 --> 00:30:32.595
Dr. Rudnick walked out of
that house. Susie Frain did not.

633
00:30:32.798 --> 00:30:35.927
And yet your own autopsy can't
determine how she was killed.

634
00:30:37.869 --> 00:30:41.829
Dr. Rudnick was hired as
your supervisor two years ago.

635
00:30:43.408 --> 00:30:44.967
Did you apply for that position?

636
00:30:45.077 --> 00:30:46.272
Yes. but that's not...

637
00:30:46.378 --> 00:30:48.074
Withdrawn. Nothing further.

638
00:30:50.015 --> 00:30:51.278
Redirect. Your Honor.

639
00:30:53.151 --> 00:30:54.949
In your opinion. could
Dr. Rudnick's wounds

640
00:30:55.053 --> 00:30:57.454
have been self-inflicted
after he killed Ms. Frain?

641
00:30:57.556 --> 00:30:59.286
Yes. Absolutely.

642
00:30:59.424 --> 00:31:01.188
Thank you. Prosecution rests.

643
00:31:02.694 --> 00:31:05.095
The defense calls
Dr. Carl Rudnick.

644
00:31:13.438 --> 00:31:16.533
Dr. Rudnick. tell the
jury. in your own words.

645
00:31:16.641 --> 00:31:19.406
what happened the night you
went to Ms. Frain's apartment.

646
00:31:20.312 --> 00:31:22.611
She attacked me
with a kitchen knife.

647
00:31:22.714 --> 00:31:24.239
There was a struggle.

648
00:31:24.349 --> 00:31:27.683
I killed her accidentally
in self-defense.

649
00:31:32.157 --> 00:31:34.854
Dr. Yates had brainwashed Susie

650
00:31:34.960 --> 00:31:36.861
into believing I'd
been setting him up.

651
00:31:36.962 --> 00:31:40.194
She accused me of tampering
with the autopsies of his victims.

652
00:31:40.298 --> 00:31:42.358
which is patently absurd.

653
00:31:42.467 --> 00:31:44.493
He'd operated in
several disparate states.

654
00:31:45.203 --> 00:31:47.297
and I made the impertinent
mistake of laughing.

655
00:31:47.406 --> 00:31:48.999
And what did she do?

656
00:31:49.441 --> 00:31:50.966
She grabbed a knife
and attacked me.

657
00:31:51.076 --> 00:31:55.514
I defended myself. resulting in
these cuts on my hand and arms.

658
00:31:56.047 --> 00:31:58.380
Could you step
down and demonstrate

659
00:31:58.483 --> 00:32:01.317
how you received those
wounds. Dr. Rudnick?

660
00:32:01.420 --> 00:32:02.649
Objection. Prejudicial.

661
00:32:02.754 --> 00:32:04.723
What? Uh. how will the jury know

662
00:32:04.823 --> 00:32:06.553
what really happened
if I can't demonstrate?

663
00:32:06.658 --> 00:32:09.457
Your Honor. I think a
demonstration could be informative.

664
00:32:09.561 --> 00:32:11.291
I'll allow it. but
don't milk it.

665
00:32:11.630 --> 00:32:12.757
(SIGHS)

666
00:32:34.953 --> 00:32:36.512
Is this how she held it?

667
00:32:36.655 --> 00:32:39.784
Yes. She pulled the knife from the
butcher block and swung it down at me.

668
00:32:39.891 --> 00:32:42.053
Like this? Yes.

669
00:32:42.160 --> 00:32:43.560
I fended her off for a moment.

670
00:32:43.662 --> 00:32:45.062
But she kept coming.

671
00:32:45.163 --> 00:32:48.133
Unfortunately. I pushed her
wrist on the downward swing.

672
00:32:48.233 --> 00:32:50.930
She'd put her body
weight into the thrust.

673
00:32:51.770 --> 00:32:55.730
and momentum drove
the knife into her left thigh.

674
00:32:58.376 --> 00:32:59.605
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

675
00:33:00.545 --> 00:33:01.740
Doctor.

676
00:33:03.381 --> 00:33:05.179
do you need a moment?

677
00:33:05.851 --> 00:33:06.851
No.

678
00:33:07.752 --> 00:33:09.118
I'm fine.

679
00:33:10.055 --> 00:33:11.421
Thank you.

680
00:33:13.291 --> 00:33:14.623
Thank you.

681
00:33:19.798 --> 00:33:20.891
(SIGHS)

682
00:33:21.833 --> 00:33:23.233
What happened next?

683
00:33:24.536 --> 00:33:27.529
Well. when I saw the blood. I
knew it had hit the femoral artery.

684
00:33:28.139 --> 00:33:30.370
I was in shock. bleeding.

685
00:33:31.042 --> 00:33:33.341
I momentarily lost
consciousness.

686
00:33:34.546 --> 00:33:36.879
And when I came to. it
was too late to save her.

687
00:33:37.115 --> 00:33:38.845
COUNSELOR CALHOUN:
And then what happened?

688
00:33:38.950 --> 00:33:42.318
I stitched my cuts because I
was afraid to go to the hospital.

689
00:33:42.420 --> 00:33:43.888
COUNSELOR CALHOUN: Why was that?

690
00:33:43.989 --> 00:33:46.288
I felt if I went in bleeding.

691
00:33:46.625 --> 00:33:48.526
no one would believe
a word I had to say.

692
00:33:48.627 --> 00:33:51.597
COUNSELOR CALHOUN: How
would you describe your state of mind?

693
00:33:51.696 --> 00:33:52.720
I was panicking.

694
00:33:53.498 --> 00:33:55.490
That's why I tried to
get rid of Susie's body.

695
00:33:55.600 --> 00:33:57.262
I'm not proud of that.

696
00:33:57.369 --> 00:34:00.601
but by then I felt the whole
system had turned against me.

697
00:34:00.705 --> 00:34:03.402
It was fight or flight.
and I chose to flee.

698
00:34:03.508 --> 00:34:06.967
And when you fled. you
disguised yourself as a woman.

699
00:34:07.078 --> 00:34:09.013
Well. everyone was
looking for Carl Rudnick.

700
00:34:09.114 --> 00:34:10.742
No one was looking for Carla.

701
00:34:11.583 --> 00:34:13.245
Seemed to be a
good idea at the time.

702
00:34:13.852 --> 00:34:15.252
Thank you. Doctor.

703
00:34:17.722 --> 00:34:19.122
Mr. Barba?

704
00:34:19.224 --> 00:34:22.683
Dr. Rudnick. are you the Deputy
Chief Medical Examiner for Manhattan?

705
00:34:22.794 --> 00:34:26.026
I was. I believe
I'm on leave now.

706
00:34:26.131 --> 00:34:27.793
As such. you would
know exactly how to

707
00:34:27.899 --> 00:34:29.765
mimic defensive
wounds. wouldn't you?

708
00:34:30.235 --> 00:34:31.312
What. are you implying that...

709
00:34:31.336 --> 00:34:32.634
Yes or no?

710
00:34:33.672 --> 00:34:34.672
Yes.

711
00:34:34.773 --> 00:34:38.107
And you would know how to
cut up and dispose of a body?

712
00:34:38.944 --> 00:34:40.913
An unfortunate area of expertise

713
00:34:41.012 --> 00:34:43.481
for someone accused
of murder. but it is mine.

714
00:34:43.582 --> 00:34:46.609
Did you use a reciprocating
saw and bolt cutter to do so?

715
00:34:46.718 --> 00:34:49.119
People's exhibit 52.

716
00:34:49.721 --> 00:34:53.089
A receipt for a
saw and bolt cutter

717
00:34:55.327 --> 00:34:56.659
from Home Depot.

718
00:34:57.596 --> 00:35:00.293
paid with Carl Rudnick's
American Express card

719
00:35:00.398 --> 00:35:04.165
at 11:50 on the night
Susie Frain was murdered.

720
00:35:05.270 --> 00:35:08.172
Yes. Luckily I was able to
make it there before closing time.

721
00:35:08.273 --> 00:35:09.273
(LAUGHS)

722
00:35:09.341 --> 00:35:11.118
As you said. you knew
exactly what you were doing.

723
00:35:11.142 --> 00:35:14.772
So it is no accident that the
one part of Susie Frain's body.

724
00:35:14.879 --> 00:35:18.338
the piece that could
confirm or refute your story.

725
00:35:18.450 --> 00:35:21.010
her left thigh. is the
part that's missing.

726
00:35:21.119 --> 00:35:22.883
Wait. you're not
suggesting I can control

727
00:35:22.988 --> 00:35:24.957
the vagaries of
the tides. are you?

728
00:35:25.490 --> 00:35:27.015
No. it is my most fervent wish

729
00:35:27.125 --> 00:35:28.354
that Susie's limb be found

730
00:35:28.460 --> 00:35:30.088
because it would
prove what I am saying.

731
00:35:30.195 --> 00:35:32.164
I mean. the angle
of the blade's entry

732
00:35:32.263 --> 00:35:34.255
would show her
wound was self-inflicted.

733
00:35:34.432 --> 00:35:36.901
Self-inflicted? Did she
dismember herself. too?

734
00:35:37.002 --> 00:35:39.631
No. obviously I did that.

735
00:35:40.305 --> 00:35:42.740
I didn't know of any other
way to get her out of there.

736
00:35:47.612 --> 00:35:48.612
That was brutal.

737
00:35:48.713 --> 00:35:50.725
Yeah. you got some good shots
in towards the end of your cross.

738
00:35:50.749 --> 00:35:53.878
Did I? Two hours. Every
time I lunged. he parried.

739
00:35:53.985 --> 00:35:55.596
The longer he was up there.
the more the jury liked him.

740
00:35:55.620 --> 00:35:57.213
How is that
possible? I don't know.

741
00:35:57.322 --> 00:35:59.767
I mean. he's peculiar. but there's
something interesting about him.

742
00:35:59.791 --> 00:36:02.236
It's weird. but at the end of our
road trip. I kind of missed the guy.

743
00:36:02.260 --> 00:36:03.751
You kind of... You
missed him? Yeah.

744
00:36:03.862 --> 00:36:05.194
I thought you two
talked too much.

745
00:36:05.363 --> 00:36:06.695
Yeah. he does talk.

746
00:36:06.798 --> 00:36:09.043
I mean. he went to the
bathroom. he was alone in the stall.

747
00:36:09.067 --> 00:36:10.307
he thought nobody was listening

748
00:36:10.435 --> 00:36:11.746
and he kept the
conversational ball rolling.

749
00:36:11.770 --> 00:36:14.706
You know what? He talks during his
autopsies. too. He records everything.

750
00:36:14.806 --> 00:36:16.283
I don't know. we
might go through them.

751
00:36:16.307 --> 00:36:17.935
see if he let something slip.

752
00:36:18.043 --> 00:36:19.602
They're city property.
Public records.

753
00:36:19.711 --> 00:36:21.951
Yeah. it's worth a shot.
Make a night out of it. Rollins?

754
00:36:24.149 --> 00:36:27.677
RUDNICK: (ON SPEAKERS)
<i>Caucasian female. late 20s. Red hair.</i>

755
00:36:28.653 --> 00:36:32.215
<i>Like so many redheads.
less susceptible to anesthesia.</i>

756
00:36:33.858 --> 00:36:37.158
<i>She felt everything that
was being done to her.</i>

757
00:36:37.862 --> 00:36:40.331
I found out why he likes
redheads. That's all I got.

758
00:36:40.432 --> 00:36:41.432
(SHUSHES)

759
00:36:44.469 --> 00:36:46.233
I think I got something.

760
00:36:46.771 --> 00:36:48.330
What. from an autopsy? No.

761
00:36:48.440 --> 00:36:50.875
Video. And it's not
from the morgue.

762
00:37:01.519 --> 00:37:04.045
<i>Given the change in
tenor of this conversation.</i>

763
00:37:04.155 --> 00:37:05.817
<i>I'm contacting my lawyer.</i>

764
00:37:06.624 --> 00:37:08.183
<i>I'd like to exercise that right.</i>

765
00:37:08.293 --> 00:37:09.488
RAFAEL: <i>Feel free.</i>

766
00:37:09.594 --> 00:37:12.894
<i>We will wait to continue
questioning you until a lawyer arrives.</i>

767
00:37:20.905 --> 00:37:22.999
<i>They can't pin these on you.</i>

768
00:37:26.010 --> 00:37:27.876
<i>Rachel's a crack whore.</i>

769
00:37:30.281 --> 00:37:32.477
<i>With the green nail polish</i>

770
00:37:33.184 --> 00:37:35.380
<i>and the proximity
to Yates' victims.</i>

771
00:37:37.188 --> 00:37:39.657
<i>that's far too much
reasonable doubt.</i>

772
00:37:39.758 --> 00:37:41.192
<i>And Lena...</i>

773
00:37:42.026 --> 00:37:44.257
<i>Nobody will buy Yates' word.</i>

774
00:37:45.063 --> 00:37:47.032
<i>My only risk there is Susie.</i>

775
00:37:47.298 --> 00:37:50.598
<i>She's dumb as a post. but she
still could put two and two together.</i>

776
00:37:51.569 --> 00:37:53.265
<i>Mmm. if she does.</i>

777
00:37:53.872 --> 00:37:57.309
(SIGHS HEAVILY) <i>I
suppose I'll have to kill her.</i>

778
00:38:00.078 --> 00:38:01.341
<i>Just like the others.</i>

779
00:38:05.583 --> 00:38:07.313
<i>Kill them all. Carl.</i>

780
00:38:10.255 --> 00:38:11.746
<i>Whatever it takes.</i>

781
00:38:14.459 --> 00:38:17.293
<i>Rita. It's very good of you
to come on such short notice.</i>

782
00:38:17.395 --> 00:38:18.906
COUNSELOR CALHOUN:
<i>Of course. Carl. But I'm afraid</i>

783
00:38:18.930 --> 00:38:19.954
<i>I have some bad news.</i>

784
00:38:20.064 --> 00:38:21.088
(TV TURNS OFF)

785
00:38:21.533 --> 00:38:23.832
This is clearly
inadmissible. Your Honor.

786
00:38:23.935 --> 00:38:26.495
I understand why
you'd like to think that.

787
00:38:27.172 --> 00:38:29.971
Walk me through the
provenance and chain of evidence.

788
00:38:30.475 --> 00:38:32.205
How did this fall
into your hands?

789
00:38:32.310 --> 00:38:34.279
We asked Dr. Rudnick
to come in for an interview.

790
00:38:34.379 --> 00:38:35.656
and he gave us
permission to record it.

791
00:38:35.680 --> 00:38:37.615
Your Honor. Dr. Rudnick
had asked for counsel.

792
00:38:37.715 --> 00:38:38.955
And when he did. we immediately

793
00:38:39.050 --> 00:38:40.294
stopped questioning
him and left the room.

794
00:38:40.318 --> 00:38:41.752
Yes. but you left the camera on.

795
00:38:41.853 --> 00:38:44.220
He knew that he
was being recorded.

796
00:38:44.322 --> 00:38:45.790
Okay. we weren't
interrogating him.

797
00:38:45.890 --> 00:38:47.916
This was a
spontaneous admission.

798
00:38:48.026 --> 00:38:49.103
Your client talks to himself.

799
00:38:49.127 --> 00:38:51.639
COUNSELOR BUCHANAN: Not
only is this inadmissible under Miranda.

800
00:38:51.663 --> 00:38:53.063
but it's also Brady material

801
00:38:53.164 --> 00:38:54.842
that should have been
made available to us.

802
00:38:54.866 --> 00:38:56.494
It was. A copy of
this video has been

803
00:38:56.601 --> 00:38:58.433
in your possession
since day one.

804
00:38:58.536 --> 00:39:00.447
You must have stopped watching
when we stopped questioning.

805
00:39:00.471 --> 00:39:01.649
JUDGE: He's right. Mr. Buchanan.

806
00:39:01.673 --> 00:39:03.266
If you turned this
off. it's on you.

807
00:39:03.374 --> 00:39:04.374
This is admissible.

808
00:39:04.475 --> 00:39:06.603
I was simply thinking out loud.

809
00:39:06.711 --> 00:39:08.839
Carl. We'll let a
jury determine that.

810
00:39:10.915 --> 00:39:13.146
You had the recording for
the entirety of my ordeal.

811
00:39:13.251 --> 00:39:14.275
and you didn't know it?

812
00:39:14.385 --> 00:39:15.478
Carl.

813
00:39:17.155 --> 00:39:18.955
Your Honor. I immediately
move for new counsel

814
00:39:18.990 --> 00:39:21.050
on the basis of
incompetent defense.

815
00:39:21.226 --> 00:39:23.661
(LAUGHS) That's your right.
I should caution you though.

816
00:39:23.761 --> 00:39:26.390
this material is admissible
no matter who defends you.

817
00:39:33.571 --> 00:39:36.769
JUDGE: Dr. Rudnick. I understand
you'd like to change your plea.

818
00:39:37.408 --> 00:39:38.740
Yes. Your Honor.

819
00:39:39.210 --> 00:39:41.611
On the charge of
murder in the first degree

820
00:39:41.713 --> 00:39:44.273
of Susie Frain.
how do you plead?

821
00:39:45.450 --> 00:39:47.078
Guilty as charged.

822
00:39:48.086 --> 00:39:49.886
JUDGE: And to the
outstanding charge of murder

823
00:39:49.954 --> 00:39:52.617
in the first degree
of Rachel Groves?

824
00:39:53.992 --> 00:39:56.484
I'm afraid I'm guilty
on that one. as well.

825
00:39:57.528 --> 00:40:01.056
Your Honor. at this time the
prosecution would like to withdraw

826
00:40:01.165 --> 00:40:03.896
its charge of murder in the
first degree of Lena Grunwald.

827
00:40:04.002 --> 00:40:05.937
All right. Counselors.
Thank you for your time.

828
00:40:06.037 --> 00:40:07.477
And now that justice
has been served.

829
00:40:07.639 --> 00:40:09.073
I declare this court adjourned.

830
00:40:09.674 --> 00:40:10.733
(GAVEL STRIKES)

831
00:40:15.914 --> 00:40:19.009
Wait. he gets away
with Lena's murder?

832
00:40:19.117 --> 00:40:21.985
Well. he'll still do 25-to-life
for the other two charges.

833
00:40:22.086 --> 00:40:24.351
Maybe you two will
be roommates one day.

834
00:40:24.522 --> 00:40:25.581
(SCOFFS)

835
00:40:25.990 --> 00:40:29.017
He did it. you know. Lena.

836
00:40:30.028 --> 00:40:31.690
He strangled her to death.

837
00:40:33.331 --> 00:40:34.890
Her skull was also fractured.

838
00:40:36.834 --> 00:40:39.030
Strangulation was
the cause of death.

839
00:40:39.437 --> 00:40:41.406
Skull fracture was postmortem.

840
00:40:43.775 --> 00:40:45.368
You sound pretty
sure about that.

841
00:40:46.144 --> 00:40:50.013
I'm just piecing it together.
but if I had to guess.

842
00:40:51.049 --> 00:40:52.745
Lena was his first time.

843
00:40:53.818 --> 00:40:55.343
Carl screwed up.

844
00:40:56.020 --> 00:41:00.822
and he had to call someone with
more experience to help him finish.

845
00:41:03.161 --> 00:41:04.993
And how did this person help?

846
00:41:05.630 --> 00:41:06.654
(CHUCKLES)

847
00:41:06.764 --> 00:41:08.699
He probably advised Carl to

848
00:41:09.734 --> 00:41:13.102
keep Lena alive
as long as possible.

849
00:41:14.138 --> 00:41:17.597
Such a waste to have
her die so quickly.

850
00:41:27.452 --> 00:41:29.444
Why are you telling me this now?

851
00:41:31.422 --> 00:41:36.360
Because I believe when
one life ends. another begins.

852
00:41:36.794 --> 00:41:39.559
You are bringing
life into this world

853
00:41:39.731 --> 00:41:42.496
just as I lost my
wife and my child.

854
00:41:44.936 --> 00:41:46.905
I feel a connection to you.

855
00:41:49.874 --> 00:41:51.775
You'll be back

856
00:41:52.810 --> 00:41:54.301
and I will be here.

857
00:42:06.324 --> 00:42:08.316
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)
